response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: FizzBuzz\", \"description\": \"Write a function that prints the numbers from 1 to 100. But for multiples of three print \\\"Fizz\\\" instead of the number and for multiples of five print \\\"Buzz\\\". For numbers which are multiples of both three and five print \\\"FizzBuzz\\\".\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```\\ndef fizzbuzz():\\n```\", \"code\": \"def fizzbuzz():\\n    for i in range(1, 101):\\n        if i % 3 == 0 and i % 5 == 0:\\n            print('FizzBuzz')\\n        elif i % 3 == 0:\\n            print('Fizz')\\n        elif i % 5 == 0:\\n            print('Buzz')\\n        else:\\n            print(i)\\n\", \"tests\": [\"print(fizzbuzz())\", \"assert 'Fizz' in str(fizzbuzz()).split('\\\\n')[2:4]\", \"assert 'Buzz' in str(fizzbuzz()).split('\\\\n')[5,6]\", \"assert 'FizzBuzz' in str(fizzbuzz()).split('\\\\n')[15]\"] }"
